Jennifer Klein, Assistant to the President and Director of the Gender Policy Council, and Tom Perez, Senior Advisor and Assistant to the President and Director of the White House Office of Intergovernmental Affairs, recently held a meeting with over 30 legislative leaders from 16 states. The purpose of the meeting was to discuss their efforts in advancing proactive legislation to protect reproductive rights in the upcoming 2024 legislative session. This meeting follows previous discussions with state legislators after the Supreme Court's decision to overturn Roe v. Wade. The White House officials expressed gratitude towards the legislators for their leadership and emphasized the importance of state partnerships in responding to attacks on reproductive freedom. They also highlighted the need for proactive legislation to ensure access to reproductive healthcare, protect patient privacy, and provide adequate training for healthcare providers.